ctronAP3000.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 35 Industrial Way, P.O. Box 5005 Rochester, NH 03867-0505 Phone: +1 603 332 9400 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
ctronAP3000.description: This mib module defines a portion of the SNMP enterprise MIBs under Enterasys Networks enterprise OID as an extension to the Enterasys AP3000 MIB. This Enterasys Networks Proprietary MIB was designed to be used for read-write access to configuration objects in AP3000.

apFilterControlBridge.name: apFilterControlBridge
apFilterControlBridge.description: This value indicates the local bridge filter setting.

enterpriseApFilterControlAPManage.name: enterpriseApFilterControlAPManage
enterpriseApFilterControlAPManage.description: This value indicates the AP management filter setting.

enterpriseApFilterControlEthernet.name: enterpriseApFilterControlEthernet
enterpriseApFilterControlEthernet.description: This value indicates the ethernet filter setting.

enterpriseApFilterProtocolTable.name: enterpriseApFilterProtocolTable
enterpriseApFilterProtocolTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of the filter protocol table.

enterpriseApFilterProtocolEntry.name: enterpriseApFilterProtocolEntry
enterpriseApFilterProtocolEntry.description: An entry in the filter protocol table, containing information about configuration of one filter table entry.

enterpriseApFilterProtocolName.name: enterpriseApFilterProtocolName
enterpriseApFilterProtocolName.description: This value indicates the name of the protocol filter. One of the following: Aironet_DDP, Appletalk_ARP, ARP, Banyan, Berkeley_Trailer_Negotiation, CDP, DEC_LAT, DEC_MOP, DEC_MOP_Dump_Load, DEC_XNS, EAPOL, Enet_Config_Test, Ethertalk, IP, LAN_Test, NetBEUI, Novell_IPX(new), Novell_IPX(old), RARP, Telxon_TXP, X.25_Level3

enterpriseApFilterProtocolISODesignator.name: enterpriseApFilterProtocolISODesignator
enterpriseApFilterProtocolISODesignator.description: This value indicates the name of the protocol filter.

enterpriseApFilterProtocolState.name: enterpriseApFilterProtocolState
enterpriseApFilterProtocolState.description: This value indicates whether the protocol filter is enabled.

apvGlobalIBSSRelayMode.name: apvGlobalIBSSRelayMode
apvGlobalIBSSRelayMode.description: This value indicates the setting of the global IBSS Relay mode among the VAPs. In Per-VAP Mode enable, the traffic between the VAPs should be blocked. In Al-VAP Mode enable, the traffic between should not be blocked.

apvFilterControlTable.name: apvFilterControlTable
apvFilterControlTable.description: Table of the control and status information about configuration of the filter Control for each Vap.

apvFilterControlEntry.name: apvFilterControlEntry
apvFilterControlEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of the filter for each Vap of the AP.

apvIBSSFilterControl.name: apvIBSSFilterControl
apvIBSSFilterControl.description: This value indicates the local bridge filter(IBSS Relay Filter) setting.

apvAPManageFilterControl.name: apvAPManageFilterControl
apvAPManageFilterControl.description: This value indicates the AP management filter setting.

comPortControl.name: comPortControl
comPortControl.description: The administrative enable/disable state for COM Port Control in a System.

macFilterTable.name: macFilterTable
macFilterTable.description: Table of status information about each configured MAC Filtering Entry.

macFilterEntry.name: macFilterEntry
macFilterEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of MAC Filter.

macFilterAddress.name: macFilterAddress
macFilterAddress.description: This values indicates the MAC address of the MAC Filter entry.

macFilterAllowedToGo.name: macFilterAllowedToGo
macFilterAllowedToGo.description: The administrative allow/deny state for that specified MAC Filter Entry.

macFilterOpeStatus.name: macFilterOpeStatus
macFilterOpeStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(0) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so differ from the following values. valid(1) - this value to indicate this entry is currently in used. invalid(2) - write this value to the corresponding entry, the whole entry will be removed. Since the order of entry shall be re-order while it has been deleted. To re-freshed the whole table is recommended for new index. create(3) - write this value to indicate that the new MAC address will be added after next writing MAC address to that new entry. The adding action will be taken on the index that grater than 1.

apMacFilterControl.name: apMacFilterControl
apMacFilterControl.description: This value indicates the control of the MAC filter setting.

apvMacFilterOperateTable.name: apvMacFilterOperateTable
apvMacFilterOperateTable.description: The Table used to manage the function in MAC Filter Table.

apvMacFilterOperateEntry.name: apvMacFilterOperateEntry
apvMacFilterOperateEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one VAP of the AP.

apvMacFilterPermission.name: apvMacFilterPermission
apvMacFilterPermission.description: This values indicates the Permission on all the active filter entry for each Vap. The negative permission will be applied on any inactive entry or any MAC that is not in the table.

apvMacFilterAddressToAdd.name: apvMacFilterAddressToAdd
apvMacFilterAddressToAdd.description: This values indicates the MAC address to be added to the local MAC filter table as an active entry for each Vap.

apvMacFilterTable.name: apvMacFilterTable
apvMacFilterTable.description: Table of status information about each configured MAC Address Filtering Entry.

apvMacFilterEntry.name: apvMacFilterEntry
apvMacFilterEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration in one radio of the AP. MacFilterEntry is created and managed using localMACFilterMgnt Table.

apvMacFilterIndex.name: apvMacFilterIndex
apvMacFilterIndex.description: MAC Filter index in each VAP.

apvMacFilterAddress.name: apvMacFilterAddress
apvMacFilterAddress.description: This values indicates the MAC address of the filter entry.

apvMacFilterActivity.name: apvMacFilterActivity
apvMacFilterActivity.description: This value indicates the Activity of the MAC table entry by the filter permission. If allow(1), the filter permission will be applied to the MAC address. If denied(2), the filter permission will not be applied to the MAC address. If delete_entry(3), the filter entry will be deleted.

qosModeControl.name: qosModeControl
qosModeControl.description: The administrative status and control of the QoS mode for the QoS management.

qosMACTypeTable.name: qosMACTypeTable
qosMACTypeTable.description: Table of status information about each configured MAC Type Entry for the QoS Management.

qosMACTypeEntry.name: qosMACTypeEntry
qosMACTypeEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration MAC Type Entry for the QoS Management.

qosMACTypeAddress.name: qosMACTypeAddress
qosMACTypeAddress.description: This values indicates the MAC address of that specified index in the entry.

qosMACTypePriority.name: qosMACTypePriority
qosMACTypePriority.description: This values indicates the level of priority of that specified MAC Address in entry.

qosMACTypeOpeStatus.name: qosMACTypeOpeStatus
qosMACTypeOpeStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(0) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so differ from the following values. valid(1) - this value to indicate this entry is currently in used. invalid(2) - write this value to the corresponding entry, the whole entry will be removed. Since the order of entry shall be re-order while it has been deleted. To re-freshed the whole table is recommended for new index. create(3) - write this value to indicate that the new MAC address will be added after next writing MAC address to that new entry. The adding action will be taken on the index that grater than 1.

qosEtherTypeTable.name: qosEtherTypeTable
qosEtherTypeTable.description: Table of status information about each configured Ether Type Entry for QoS Management.

qosEtherTypeEntry.name: qosEtherTypeEntry
qosEtherTypeEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration Ether Type for QoS Management.

qosEtherTypeIndex.name: qosEtherTypeIndex
qosEtherTypeIndex.description: Qos Ether Type index in the table.

qosEtherTypeHexValue.name: qosEtherTypeHexValue
qosEtherTypeHexValue.description: The Hex Value to indicate the type of Ether of that specified index in the entry.

qosEtherTypePriority.name: qosEtherTypePriority
qosEtherTypePriority.description: This values indicates the level of priority of that specified MAC Address in entry.

qosEtherTypeOpeStatus.name: qosEtherTypeOpeStatus
qosEtherTypeOpeStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(0) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so differ from the following values. valid(1) - this value to indicate this entry is currently in used. invalid(2) - write this value to the corresponding entry, the whole entry will be removed. Since the order of entry shall be re-order while it has been deleted. To re-freshed the whole table is recommended for new index. create(3) - write this value to indicate that the new Ether Value will be added after next writing Ether Type Value to that new entry. The adding action will be taken on the index that grater than 1.

qosQueueingMode.name: qosQueueingMode
qosQueueingMode.description: The administrative control of the QoS Queuing mode for the QoS management.

qosSVPStatus.name: qosSVPStatus
qosSVPStatus.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SVP.

linkQualityTable.name: linkQualityTable
linkQualityTable.description: Table of status information about the radio Interface Link Quality Entry.

linkQualityEntry.name: linkQualityEntry
linkQualityEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of the radio Interface Link Quality.

linkQualityRadioIndex.name: linkQualityRadioIndex
linkQualityRadioIndex.description: This is the value to define the index of the radio interface.

linkQualityStaIndex.name: linkQualityStaIndex
linkQualityStaIndex.description: This is value to define the index of link station.

linkQualityStaMacAddress.name: linkQualityStaMacAddress
linkQualityStaMacAddress.description: This values indicates the MAC address of the link station.

linkQualityStaRssi.name: linkQualityStaRssi
linkQualityStaRssi.description: This values indicates the percentage RSSI of the link station.

trapLocalMacAddrAuthSuccess.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP localMacAddrAuthSuccess trap.

trapDot1xAuthNotInitiated.name: trapDot1xAuthNotInitiated
trapDot1xAuthNotInitiated.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP dot1xAuthNotInitiated trap.

trapDot1xAuthSuccess.name: trapDot1xAuthSuccess
trapDot1xAuthSuccess.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP dot1xAuthSuccess trap.

trapDot1xAuthFail.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP dot1xAuthFail trap.

trapDot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess.name: trapDot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess
trapDot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP dot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess trap.

trapDot1xMacAddrAuthFail.name: trapDot1xMacAddrAuthFail
trapDot1xMacAddrAuthFail.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP dot1xMacAddrAuthFail trap.

trapPppLogonFail.name: trapPppLogonFail
trapPppLogonFail.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP pppLogonFail trap.

trapIappStationRoamedFrom.name: trapIappStationRoamedFrom
trapIappStationRoamedFrom.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP iappStationRoamedFrom trap.

trapIappStationRoamedTo.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP iappStationRoamedFrom trap.

trapIappContextDataSent.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP iappContextDataSent trap.

trapSntpServerFail.name: trapSntpServerFail
trapSntpServerFail.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP sntpServerFail trap.

trapDot11InterfaceAFail.name: trapDot11InterfaceAFail
trapDot11InterfaceAFail.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP dot11InterfaceAFail trap.

trapDot11InterfaceGFail.name: trapDot11InterfaceGFail
trapDot11InterfaceGFail.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP dot11InterfaceGFail trap.

trapDot11WirelessSTPDetection.name: trapDot11WirelessSTPDetection
trapDot11WirelessSTPDetection.description: The administrative enable/disable state for SNMP dot11WirelessSTPDetection trap.

apSnmpTrapDestinationTable.name: apSnmpTrapDestinationTable
apSnmpTrapDestinationTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each trap receiving server.

apSnmpTrapDestinationEntry.name: apSnmpTrapDestinationEntry
apSnmpTrapDestinationEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one trap receiving server.

apSnmpTrapDestinationIndex.name: apSnmpTrapDestinationIndex
apSnmpTrapDestinationIndex.description: Index of the Trap Destination Table.

apSnmpTrapDestinationIP.name: apSnmpTrapDestinationIP
apSnmpTrapDestinationIP.description: The IP address of the trap receiving server.

apSnmpTrapDestinationState.name: apSnmpTrapDestinationState
apSnmpTrapDestinationState.description: This value indicates whether the trap receiving server is enabled.

apSnmpCommunityReadOnly.name: apSnmpCommunityReadOnly
apSnmpCommunityReadOnly.description: The SNMP Read Only Community. The value if read, will only show ******.

apSnmpCommunityReadWrite.name: apSnmpCommunityReadWrite
apSnmpCommunityReadWrite.description: The SNMP Read Write Community. The value if read, will only show *****.

apSnmpVersionFilter.name: apSnmpVersionFilter
apSnmpVersionFilter.description: To set the version-filter of SNMP.

swHardwareVer.name: swHardwareVer
swHardwareVer.description: Hardware version of the main board.

swBootRomVer.name: swBootRomVer
swBootRomVer.description: Boot ROM code version of the main board.

swOpCodeVer.name: swOpCodeVer
swOpCodeVer.description: Operation code version of the main board.

swSerialNumber.name: swSerialNumber
swSerialNumber.description: Serial Number of the Access Point.

swProductName.name: swProductName
swProductName.description: The Product Name of the Access Point.

swCountrySetting.name: swCountrySetting
swCountrySetting.description: The current CountryCode Setting of the Access Point.

apRadioSecurityTable.name: apRadioSecurityTable
apRadioSecurityTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each radio in terms of security settings.

apRadioSecurityEntry.name: apRadioSecurityEntry
apRadioSecurityEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one radio of the AP.

apRadioSecurityWEPAuthType.name: apRadioSecurityWEPAuthType
apRadioSecurityWEPAuthType.description: This value indicates the type of WEP authentication in use for this radio interface. opensystem(0) Set authentication open sharedkey(1) Set authentication shared wpa(2) Set WPA Mode wpapsk(3) Set WPA-PSK Mode wpa-wpa2-mixed(4) Set WPA-WPA2-Mixed Mode wpawpa2pskmixed(5) Set WPA-WPA2 PSK Mixed Mode wpa2(6) Set WPA2 Mode wpa2psk(7) Set WPA2-PSK Mode

apRadioSecuritySharedKeyLen.name: apRadioSecuritySharedKeyLen
apRadioSecuritySharedKeyLen.description: This value indicates the shared key length for this radio interface.

apRadioSecurityWPAMode.name: apRadioSecurityWPAMode
apRadioSecurityWPAMode.description: This value indicates the state of WPA for this radio interface.

apRadioSecurityWPAKeyType.name: apRadioSecurityWPAKeyType
apRadioSecurityWPAKeyType.description: This value indicates the type of WPA Key Management in use for this radio interface.

apRadioSecurityWPACipher.name: apRadioSecurityWPACipher
apRadioSecurityWPACipher.description: This value indicates the type of WPA Cipher in use for this radio interface.

apRadioSecurityWPAPSKType.name: apRadioSecurityWPAPSKType
apRadioSecurityWPAPSKType.description: This value indicates the type of WPA Pre Shared Key in use for this radio interface.

apRadioSecurityWPAPSK.name: apRadioSecurityWPAPSK
apRadioSecurityWPAPSK.description: This value indicates WPA Pre Shared Key in use for this radio interface.

apRadioSecurityWEPKeyType.name: apRadioSecurityWEPKeyType
apRadioSecurityWEPKeyType.description: This value indicates the type of WEP Key in use for this radio interface.

apRadioSecurityWEPEnabled.name: apRadioSecurityWEPEnabled
apRadioSecurityWEPEnabled.description: This value indicates whether WEP is enabled.

apRadioSecurityWPACipherSuite.name: apRadioSecurityWPACipherSuite
apRadioSecurityWPACipherSuite.description: This value indicates the type of WPA Cipher Suite in use for this radio interface.

apSecuritySshServerEnabled.name: apSecuritySshServerEnabled
apSecuritySshServerEnabled.description: This value indicates whether SSH server is enabled.

apSecuritySshServerPort.name: apSecuritySshServerPort
apSecuritySshServerPort.description: This value indicates SSH server's port number.

apSecuritySshTelnetServerEnabled.name: apSecuritySshTelnetServerEnabled
apSecuritySshTelnetServerEnabled.description: This value indicates whether telnet server is enabled.

enterpriseApRadioTable.name: enterpriseApRadioTable
enterpriseApRadioTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each radio.

enterpriseApRadioEntry.name: enterpriseApRadioEntry
enterpriseApRadioEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one radio of the AP.

enterpriseApRadioAutoChannel.name: enterpriseApRadioAutoChannel
enterpriseApRadioAutoChannel.description: This value indicates whether auto channel selection is enabled or not for this radio interface

enterpriseApRadioTransmitPower.name: enterpriseApRadioTransmitPower
enterpriseApRadioTransmitPower.description: This value indicates the transmit power for this radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioTurboMode.name: enterpriseApRadioTurboMode
enterpriseApRadioTurboMode.description: This value indicates whether turbo mode is enabled for this radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioDataRate.name: enterpriseApRadioDataRate
enterpriseApRadioDataRate.description: This value indicates the data rate for this radio interface. Radio interface A operates at 6, 9, 12, 18, 24, 36, 48, 54. Radio interface G operates all listed data rates. The auto setting will attempt to set the best data rate for the interface

enterpriseApRadioGMode.name: enterpriseApRadioGMode
enterpriseApRadioGMode.description: This value indicates the radio mode for the 802.11g radio. This setting is only valid for the 802.11g interface.

enterpriseApRadioAntennaMode.name: enterpriseApRadioAntennaMode
enterpriseApRadioAntennaMode.description: This value indicates the antenna mode in use for the G-radio. The values are interpreted as follows: both(1) means use both built-in antennas, left(2) means use left side. right(3) means use right side. invalid(4) means not support. This setting is only valid for the 802.11g interface.

rogueApState.name: rogueApState
rogueApState.description: This value is used to enable/disable Rogue Ap Detection for this radio interface.

rogueApInterval.name: rogueApInterval
rogueApInterval.description: How often to scan for Rogue Aps. The interval in minutes, with default of 720(minutes).

rogueApDuration.name: rogueApDuration
rogueApDuration.description: How long to scan each channel (in milliseconds). A longer duration will yield more complete results. A shorter duration will allow clients a better chance of remaining connected. Default value is 350(milliseconds).

rogueApScanNow.name: rogueApScanNow
rogueApScanNow.description: When writing the value to enable, the AP will trigger the Rouge AP scan function. The value will always return disable(2).

enterpriseApRadioAntennaModeControl.name: enterpriseApRadioAntennaModeControl
enterpriseApRadioAntennaModeControl.description: This value indicates which antenna is in use for the radio Interface. The values are interpreted as follows: fixed(1) specify to use built-in antennas, external(2) specify to use one external antenna.

enterpriseApRadioFixedAntennaType.name: enterpriseApRadioFixedAntennaType
enterpriseApRadioFixedAntennaType.description: This value indicates which antenna type is in use as the fixed antenna is selected.

enterpriseApRadioAntennaID.name: enterpriseApRadioAntennaID
enterpriseApRadioAntennaID.description: This value indicates which antenna ID will be in use for the radio Interface.

enterpriseApRadioMulticastDataRate.name: enterpriseApRadioMulticastDataRate
enterpriseApRadioMulticastDataRate.description: This value indicates the data rate for mc/bc packets from this radio interface. sixMbps(6), nineMbps(9), twelveMbps(12), eighteenMbps(18), twentyFourMbps(24), thirtySixMbps(36), fortyEightMbps(48), and fiftyFourMbps(54) are for 11a and g-only mode. The default for b-only and b+g mode is oneMbps(1), twoMbps(2), fiveAndHalfMbps(5) and elevenMbps(11).

enterpriseApRadioAutoDataRate.name: enterpriseApRadioAutoDataRate
enterpriseApRadioAutoDataRate.description: This value indicates whether automated data rate is enabled or not for this radio interface

enterpriseApRadioPreamble.name: enterpriseApRadioPreamble
enterpriseApRadioPreamble.description: This value indicates the preamble length of 11g. The values are interpreted as follows: long(1) sets the preamble length to long. short(2) sets the preamble length to short. invalid(3) means not support. This setting is only valid for the 802.11g interface.

enterpriseApRadioSWRetryMode.name: enterpriseApRadioSWRetryMode
enterpriseApRadioSWRetryMode.description: This value indicates whether SW retty mode is enabled or not for this radio interface

enterpriseApVapRadioTable.name: enterpriseApVapRadioTable
enterpriseApVapRadioTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each Vap radio.

enterpriseApVapRadioEntry.name: enterpriseApVapRadioEntry
enterpriseApVapRadioEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one Vap radio of the AP.

enterpriseApVapRadioState.name: enterpriseApVapRadioState
enterpriseApVapRadioState.description: This value indicates the state of the radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioSecureAccess.name: enterpriseApVapRadioSecureAccess
enterpriseApVapRadioSecureAccess.description: This value indicates whether secure access is enabled for this radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioMaxAssoc.name: enterpriseApVapRadioMaxAssoc
enterpriseApVapRadioMaxAssoc.description: This value indicates the max number of clients allowed on this radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioTransmitKey.name: enterpriseApVapRadioTransmitKey
enterpriseApVapRadioTransmitKey.description: This value indicates default transmit key in use for this radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioDescription.name: enterpriseApVapRadioDescription
enterpriseApVapRadioDescription.description: This value indicates the description for this radio interface.

enterpriseApVapRadioDefefaultPriority.name: enterpriseApVapRadioDefefaultPriority
enterpriseApVapRadioDefefaultPriority.description: This values indicates the level of default priority of that specified VAP in entry.

enterpriseApRadioWdsTable.name: enterpriseApRadioWdsTable
enterpriseApRadioWdsTable.description: Table of configuration information for Wds for each Radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioWdsEntry.name: enterpriseApRadioWdsEntry
enterpriseApRadioWdsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of peer Bridging for one radio of the AP. The table is indexed by radio Index (corresponding to enterpriseApRadioTable). The table does not contain the radio index as a member of the table.

wdsApRole.name: wdsApRole
wdsApRole.description: This value indicates the role of the Ap for this radio, roleAp(1): AP operation. roleBridgeMaster(2): Root-Bridge mode. roleBridge(3): Bridge Mode.

wdsApAckTimeout.name: wdsApAckTimeout
wdsApAckTimeout.description: This value indicates the WDS Ack timeout for this radio in us, and the following values can be set to the system: 0 Set wireless Ack Timeout as system default 20 0 to 1 miles: Ack timeout is 20 us 40 1 to 3 miles: Ack timeout is 40 us 75 3 to 6 miles: Ack timeout is 75 us 115 6 to 10 miles: Ack timeout is 115 us

enterpriseApRadioWdsPeerTable.name: enterpriseApRadioWdsPeerTable
enterpriseApRadioWdsPeerTable.description: Table of configuration information for Wds Peers for each Radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioWdsPeerEntry.name: enterpriseApRadioWdsPeerEntry
enterpriseApRadioWdsPeerEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of peer Bridging for one radio of the AP. The table is indexed by radio Index (corresponding to enterpriseApRadioTable) and the peer index (Up to 8). The table does not contain the radio index as a member of the table.

wdsPeerIndex.name: wdsPeerIndex
wdsPeerIndex.description: Peer Index for the radio interface.

wdsPeerRSSI.name: wdsPeerRSSI
wdsPeerRSSI.description: This value indicates the RSSI value of the WDS peer link.

enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysTable.name: enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysTable
enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysTable.description: Conceptual table for WEP default keys.

enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysEntry.name: enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysEntry
enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the WEP Default Keys Table. A collection of objects containing information used to determine if a WEPkey as been defined and if so, the value of the WEPkey.

enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysIndex.name: enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysIndex
enterpriseApRadioWEPKeysIndex.description: WEP Key Index for the radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioWEPKeyType.name: enterpriseApRadioWEPKeyType
enterpriseApRadioWEPKeyType.description: status of the WEP Key type

enterpriseApRadioWEPKeyLength.name: enterpriseApRadioWEPKeyLength
enterpriseApRadioWEPKeyLength.description: status of the WEP Key Length.

enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaListTable.name: enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaListTable
enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaListTable.description: Conceptual table for Available Antenna List used in the Radio.

enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaListEntry.name: enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaListEntry
enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaListEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the Antenna List Table. A collection of objects containing information used to show if an Antenna as been defined and if so, the value of the antenna Id.

enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaIndex.name: enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaIndex
enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaIndex.description: Available Antenna List Index for the radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaId.name: enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaId
enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaId.description: Available antenna Id in the entry.

enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaDesc.name: enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaDesc
enterpriseApRadioAvAntennaDesc.description: The description of the antenna ID.

enterpriseApRadioAvChannelListTable.name: enterpriseApRadioAvChannelListTable
enterpriseApRadioAvChannelListTable.description: Conceptual table for Available Channel List used in the Radio.

enterpriseApRadioAvChannelListEntry.name: enterpriseApRadioAvChannelListEntry
enterpriseApRadioAvChannelListEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the Channel List Table. A collection of objects containing information used to show if a Channel No. as been defined and if so, the value of the Channel No.

enterpriseApRadioAvChannelIndex.name: enterpriseApRadioAvChannelIndex
enterpriseApRadioAvChannelIndex.description: Channel List Index for the radio interface.

enterpriseApRadioAvChannelNo.name: enterpriseApRadioAvChannelNo
enterpriseApRadioAvChannelNo.description: Available channel number in the entry

netConfigIPAddress.name: netConfigIPAddress
netConfigIPAddress.description: The IP address of this Net interface. The default value for this object is 0.0.0.0. If either the netConfigIPAddress or netConfigSubnetMask are 0.0.0.0, then when the device boots, it may use DHCP to try to figure out what these values should be. If DHCP fails, before the device can talk on the network, this value must be configured (e.g., through a terminal attached to the device).

netConfigSubnetMask.name: netConfigSubnetMask
netConfigSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask of this Net interface. The default value for this object is 0.0.0.0. If either the netConfigIPAddress or netConfigSubnetMask are 0.0.0.0, then when the device boots, it may use DHCP to try to figure out what these values should be. If DHCP fails, before the device can talk on the network, this value must be configured (e.g., through a terminal attached to the device).

netConfigDefaultGateway.name: netConfigDefaultGateway
netConfigDefaultGateway.description: The IP Address of the default gateway. If this value is undefined or unknown, it shall have the value 0.0.0.0.

netConfigHttpsPort.name: netConfigHttpsPort
netConfigHttpsPort.description: The port number for Secure HTTP.

apVLANMgntNativeId.name: apVLANMgntNativeId
apVLANMgntNativeId.description: This value indicates the native VLAN Id.

apVLANMgntState.name: apVLANMgntState
apVLANMgntState.description: This value indicates whether VLANs are enabled or disabled.

apVLANMgntStateNextBoot.name: apVLANMgntStateNextBoot
apVLANMgntStateNextBoot.description: This value indicates the VLANs state for the next reset.

apVLANMgntEtherUntaggedVlanId.name: apVLANMgntEtherUntaggedVlanId
apVLANMgntEtherUntaggedVlanId.description: This value indicates the Untagged VlanID for Ether Interface.

apNativeVlanTable.name: apNativeVlanTable
apNativeVlanTable.description: Table used to manage the Vlans for each wireless interface.

apNativeVlanEntry.name: apNativeVlanEntry
apNativeVlanEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about VLAN configuration of one wireless interface.

apNativeVlanIfIndex.name: apNativeVlanIfIndex
apNativeVlanIfIndex.description: Interface Index of the wireless interface for which the VLAN is assigned to.

apNativeVlanSsidNumber.name: apNativeVlanSsidNumber
apNativeVlanSsidNumber.description: Associated Number for Service Set Id (SSID) of the wireless interface for which the VLAN is assigned to. Note: This is for future support of multiple SSIDs per radio interface.

apNativeVlanVlanId.name: apNativeVlanVlanId
apNativeVlanVlanId.description: This value indicates the native VLAN Id of the wireless interface associated with the if index and the SSID number(if it is not 0).

apNativeVlanState.name: apNativeVlanState
apNativeVlanState.description: This value indicates the Native VLANs state.

ap8021xState.name: ap8021xState
ap8021xState.description: This attribute indicates that the Enterprise the state of the 802.1X authentication algorithm.

ap8021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate.name: ap8021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate
ap8021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate.description: The number (in minutes) between changing the broadcast key for 802.1X and WPA clients

ap8021xSessionKeyRefreshRate.name: ap8021xSessionKeyRefreshRate
ap8021xSessionKeyRefreshRate.description: The number (in minutes) between changing session keys for 802.1X and WPA clients

ap8021xReauthenticationTimeout.name: ap8021xReauthenticationTimeout
ap8021xReauthenticationTimeout.description: The number (in minutes) between forcing 802.1X clients to reauthenticate

apAuthenticationMode.name: apAuthenticationMode
apAuthenticationMode.description: This value indicates the type of MAC authentication or RADIUS authentication in use, or not in use.

apAuthenticationServerTable.name: apAuthenticationServerTable
apAuthenticationServerTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each authentication server.

apAuthenticationServerEntry.name: apAuthenticationServerEntry
apAuthenticationServerEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one authentication server of the AP.

apAuthenticationServer.name: apAuthenticationServer
apAuthenticationServer.description: This value indicates the IP address or host name of the authentication server.

apAuthenticationPort.name: apAuthenticationPort
apAuthenticationPort.description: This value indicates the UDP Port used by the authentication server.

apAuthenticationKey.name: apAuthenticationKey
apAuthenticationKey.description: This value indicates the shared key used by the authentication server.

apAuthenticationRetransmit.name: apAuthenticationRetransmit
apAuthenticationRetransmit.description: This value indicates the retransmit timer length used by the authentication server.

apAuthenticationTimeout.name: apAuthenticationTimeout
apAuthenticationTimeout.description: This value indicates the Timeout value(sec) used by the authentication server.

apAuthenticationAcctPort.name: apAuthenticationAcctPort
apAuthenticationAcctPort.description: UDP Accounting Port. The valid range is from 1024-65535. A value of 0 means accounting is disabled.

apAuthenticationAcctInterimUpdate.name: apAuthenticationAcctInterimUpdate
apAuthenticationAcctInterimUpdate.description: The interval between sending accounting updates.

apAuthenticationAcctState.name: apAuthenticationAcctState
apAuthenticationAcctState.description: This value indicates whether the Accounting Server is enabled.

apAuthenticationSupplicantTable.name: apAuthenticationSupplicantTable
apAuthenticationSupplicantTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of supplicant

apAuthenticationSupplicantEntry.name: apAuthenticationSupplicantEntry
apAuthenticationSupplicantEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one supplicant.

ap8021xSuppIndex.name: ap8021xSuppIndex
ap8021xSuppIndex.description: Index of the interface for which this supplicant is running. Currently only the ethernet interface.

ap8021xSuppState.name: ap8021xSuppState
ap8021xSuppState.description: This object is used to enable or disable the 802.1X supplicant.

ap8021xSuppUser.name: ap8021xSuppUser
ap8021xSuppUser.description: This value indicates the username for supplicant. If value is configured, will display ****. Else will display EMPTY.

ap8021xSuppPasswd.name: ap8021xSuppPasswd
ap8021xSuppPasswd.description: This value indicates the password for supplicant. If value is configured, will display ****. Else will display EMPTY.

apvAuthenticationSetupTable.name: apvAuthenticationSetupTable
apvAuthenticationSetupTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of 8021x for each Vap.

apvAuthenticationSetupEntry.name: apvAuthenticationSetupEntry
apvAuthenticationSetupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of 8021x for each Vap of the AP.

apv8021xState.name: apv8021xState
apv8021xState.description: This attribute indicates that the Enterprise the state of the 802.1X authentication algorithm.

apv8021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate.name: apv8021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate
apv8021xBroadcastKeyRefreshRate.description: The number (in minutes) between changing the broadcast key for 802.1X and WPA clients

apv8021xSessionKeyRefreshRate.name: apv8021xSessionKeyRefreshRate
apv8021xSessionKeyRefreshRate.description: The number (in minutes) between changing history keys for 802.1X and WPA clients

apv8021xReauthenticationTimeout.name: apv8021xReauthenticationTimeout
apv8021xReauthenticationTimeout.description: The number (in minutes) between forcing 802.1X clients to reauthenticate

apvMACAuthenticationMode.name: apvMACAuthenticationMode
apvMACAuthenticationMode.description: This value indicates the mode of MAC authentication in use.

apvMACAuthenticationTimeout.name: apvMACAuthenticationTimeout
apvMACAuthenticationTimeout.description: The number (in minutes) between forcing RADIUS MAC to authenticate.

apvMACAuthenticationPasswd.name: apvMACAuthenticationPasswd
apvMACAuthenticationPasswd.description: This value indicates the password for MAC RADIUS Authentication. If value is configured, will display ****. Else will display EMPTY.

apWStationSessionTable.name: apWStationSessionTable
apWStationSessionTable.description: This table list all sessions (wireless stations) status

apWStationSessionEntry.name: apWStationSessionEntry
apWStationSessionEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about status and statistics of the wireless station.

apWStationSessionIfIndex.name: apWStationSessionIfIndex
apWStationSessionIfIndex.description: Interface index for the radio this session is associated with.

apWStationSessionStationAddres.name: apWStationSessionStationAddres
apWStationSessionStationAddres.description: The unique MAC Address of the station for this session.

apWStationSessionAuthenticated.name: apWStationSessionAuthenticated
apWStationSessionAuthenticated.description: Whether the session is authenticated or not.

apWStationSessionAssociated.name: apWStationSessionAssociated
apWStationSessionAssociated.description: Whether the session is associated or not. It is rare case that not associated stations show up in the table.

apWStationSessionIsForwarding.name: apWStationSessionIsForwarding
apWStationSessionIsForwarding.description: Whether the AP is forwarding the client station traffic (higher level authentication)

apWStationSessionKeyType.name: apWStationSessionKeyType
apWStationSessionKeyType.description: The encryption key type used by the station. Note that wpa-wep is not supported

apWStationSessionLastAuthenticatedTime.name: apWStationSessionLastAuthenticatedTime
apWStationSessionLastAuthenticatedTime.description: This is the time in hundredths of a second last time the client is authenticated. Note that a session may be authenticated multiple times. The value is related to the system startup

apWStationSessionAssociatedTime.name: apWStationSessionAssociatedTime
apWStationSessionAssociatedTime.description: This is the time in hundredths of a second since the client associated. The value is related to the system startup

apWStationSessionLastAssociatedTime.name: apWStationSessionLastAssociatedTime
apWStationSessionLastAssociatedTime.description: This is the time in hundredths of a second when the client associated in last session. The value is related to the system startup

apWStationSessionLastDisassociatedTime.name: apWStationSessionLastDisassociatedTime
apWStationSessionLastDisassociatedTime.description: This is the time in hundredths of a second when the client disassociated in last session. The value is related to the system startup

apWStationSessionTxPacketCount.name: apWStationSessionTxPacketCount
apWStationSessionTxPacketCount.description: This is the number of packets transmitted from the client to the AP. It includes data, control and management packets.

apWStationSessionRxPacketCount.name: apWStationSessionRxPacketCount
apWStationSessionRxPacketCount.description: This is the number of unicast packets transmitted from the AP to the client. It includes data, control and management packets.

apWStationSessionTxByteCount.name: apWStationSessionTxByteCount
apWStationSessionTxByteCount.description: This is the number of bytes transmitted from the client to the AP. It includes the bytes of data, control and management packets.

apWStationSessionRxByteCount.name: apWStationSessionRxByteCount
apWStationSessionRxByteCount.description: This is the number of unicast bytes transmitted from the AP to the client. It includes the bytes of data, control and management packets.

apWStationSessionVlanID.name: apWStationSessionVlanID
apWStationSessionVlanID.description: The current VLAN Id used by the station.

rogueApDetectionTable.name: rogueApDetectionTable
rogueApDetectionTable.description: Table of each AP that has been detected.

rogueApDetectionEntry.name: rogueApDetectionEntry
rogueApDetectionEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about any AP detected.

rogueApRADIUSAuthenticate.name: rogueApRADIUSAuthenticate
rogueApRADIUSAuthenticate.description: Value is used to enable/disable RADIUS Authentication.

rogueApClear.name: rogueApClear
rogueApClear.description: This object is set to clear(1) to clear the Rogue AP detection table. When read, the value will have no meaning.

apAdminUsername.name: apAdminUsername
apAdminUsername.description: This value indicates the username for management login.

appAdminPassword.name: appAdminPassword
appAdminPassword.description: This value indicates the password for management login.

apRestartOpCodeFile.name: apRestartOpCodeFile
apRestartOpCodeFile.description: Name of op-code file for start-up.

apRestartControl.name: apRestartControl
apRestartControl.description: Setting this object to warmBoot(2) causes the device to restart the application software with current configuration parameters saved in non-volatile memory. Setting this object to coldBoot(3) causes the device to reinitialize configuration parameters in non-volatile memory to default values and restart the application software. When the device is running normally, this variable has a value of running(1).

apSNTPState.name: apSNTPState
apSNTPState.description: This value indicates whether SNTP is enabled or not. At least one of the SNTP servers must have a valid IP address before SNTP can be enabled.

apSNTPPrimaryServer.name: apSNTPPrimaryServer
apSNTPPrimaryServer.description: This value indicates the IP address of the primary SNTP server.

apSNTPSecondaryServer.name: apSNTPSecondaryServer
apSNTPSecondaryServer.description: This value indicates the IP address of the secondary SNTP server.

apSNTPTimezone.name: apSNTPTimezone
apSNTPTimezone.description: This value indicates which timezone to use.

apSNTPDST.name: apSNTPDST
apSNTPDST.description: This value indicates whether Daylight Savings Time is enabled or not.

apSNTPDSTStartMonth.name: apSNTPDSTStartMonth
apSNTPDSTStartMonth.description: This value indicates the starting month for Daylight Savings Time.

apSNTPDSTStartDay.name: apSNTPDSTStartDay
apSNTPDSTStartDay.description: This value indicates the starting day for Daylight Savings Time.

apSNTPDSTEndMonth.name: apSNTPDSTEndMonth
apSNTPDSTEndMonth.description: This value indicates the ending month for Daylight Savings Time.

apSNTPDSTEndDay.name: apSNTPDSTEndDay
apSNTPDSTEndDay.description: This value indicates the ending day for Daylight Savings Time.

apDNSPrimaryServer.name: apDNSPrimaryServer
apDNSPrimaryServer.description: This value indicates the IP address of the primary DNS server.

apDNSSecondaryServer.name: apDNSSecondaryServer
apDNSSecondaryServer.description: This value indicates the IP address of the secondary DNS server.

apLogConfigState.name: apLogConfigState
apLogConfigState.description: This value indicates whether syslog is enabled.

apSyslogConsoleState.name: apSyslogConsoleState
apSyslogConsoleState.description: This value indicates whether syslog console logging is enabled.

apSyslogLevel.name: apSyslogLevel
apSyslogLevel.description: This value indicates the syslog logging level.

apSyslogServerTable.name: apSyslogServerTable
apSyslogServerTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about configuration of each syslog server.

apSyslogServerEntry.name: apSyslogServerEntry
apSyslogServerEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about configuration of one syslog server of the AP.

apSyslogServerState.name: apSyslogServerState
apSyslogServerState.description: This value indicates whether the syslog server is enabled.

apSyslogServerIPAddress.name: apSyslogServerIPAddress
apSyslogServerIPAddress.description: This value indicates the IP address of the syslog server.

apSyslogServerPort.name: apSyslogServerPort
apSyslogServerPort.description: This value indicates the UDP Port used by the syslog server.

apEventLogTable.name: apEventLogTable
apEventLogTable.description: This table is a snapshot of the current event log.

apEventLogEntry.name: apEventLogEntry
apEventLogEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing one message from the event log.

apEventLogIndex.name: apEventLogIndex
apEventLogIndex.description: Index of the Event Log Message

apEventLogClear.name: apEventLogClear
apEventLogClear.description: This object is set to 1 to clear the event log. When read, the value will have no meaning.

apWSLSupportControl.name: apWSLSupportControl
apWSLSupportControl.description: The administrative enable/disable state for the control of the WSL function.

apWSLSupportMasterAddress.name: apWSLSupportMasterAddress
apWSLSupportMasterAddress.description: This value indicates IP address of the main WSL.

apWSLSupportSecondaryAddress.name: apWSLSupportSecondaryAddress
apWSLSupportSecondaryAddress.description: This value indicates IP address of the peer WSL.

apWSLSupportPort.name: apWSLSupportPort
apWSLSupportPort.description: This value indicates the TCP Port used by the WSL server.

apWSLSupportHeartbeatInterval.name: apWSLSupportHeartbeatInterval
apWSLSupportHeartbeatInterval.description: This value indicates the WSL Heartbeat Interval.

apWSLSupportHeartbeatLastChange.name: apWSLSupportHeartbeatLastChange
apWSLSupportHeartbeatLastChange.description: The sysUpTime at which the Heartbeat was last modified. The format is defined as hh:mm:ss - dd:mm:yy

apWSLSupportOperationMode.name: apWSLSupportOperationMode
apWSLSupportOperationMode.description: This attribute indicates that the WSL Operation Mode in 0: AP in standalone mode, or 1: AP in ETS WSL managed mode (associated mode).

apWSLSupportRxThreshold.name: apWSLSupportRxThreshold
apWSLSupportRxThreshold.description: This value indicates the WSL CCA rejection threshold in dBm scale.

apWSLSupportControlStatus.name: apWSLSupportControlStatus
apWSLSupportControlStatus.description: The operative enable/disable state for the control of the WSL function.

apWSLRFAreaPollControl.name: apWSLRFAreaPollControl
apWSLRFAreaPollControl.description: The administrative enable/disable state for the control of the WSL RF Area Poll function.

apWSLRFAreaPollControlStatus.name: apWSLRFAreaPollControlStatus
apWSLRFAreaPollControlStatus.description: The operative enable/disable state for the control of the WSL RF Area Poll function.

apWMMControlTable.name: apWMMControlTable
apWMMControlTable.description: Table for WMM configuration per radio.

apWMMState.name: apWMMState
apWMMState.description: This value indicates the WMM state.

apWMMBssParamTable.name: apWMMBssParamTable
apWMMBssParamTable.description: Conceptual table for EDCA default parameter values at a non-AP QSTA. This table shall contain the four entries of the EDCA parameters corresponding to four possible ACs (access category): 1) AC_BE (best effort, ACI=0) 2) AC_BK (background, ACI=1) 3) AC_VI (video, ACI=2) 4) AC_VO (voice, ACI=3)

apWMMBssParamEntry.name: apWMMBssParamEntry
apWMMBssParamEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the apWMMBssParamTable. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

apWMMBssParamIndex.name: apWMMBssParamIndex
apWMMBssParamIndex.description: The index used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the apWMMBssParam Table. The value of this variable is 1) 1 AC_BE (best effort, ACI=0) 2) 2 AC_BK (background, ACI=1) 3) 3 AC_VI (video, ACI=2) 4) 4 AC_VO (voice, ACI=3)

apWMMBssParamCWmin.name: apWMMBssParamCWmin
apWMMBssParamCWmin.description: This attribute shall specify the value of the minimum size of the window in the exponent form that shall be used by a QSTA for a particular AC for generating a random number for the backoff.

apWMMBssParamCWmax.name: apWMMBssParamCWmax
apWMMBssParamCWmax.description: This attribute shall specify the value of the maximum size of the window in the exponent form that shall be used by a QSTA for a particular AC for generating a random number for the backoff.

apWMMBssParamAIFSN.name: apWMMBssParamAIFSN
apWMMBssParamAIFSN.description: This attribute shall specify the number of slots, after a SIFS duration, that the QSTA, for a particular AC, shall sense the medium idle either before transmitting or executing a backoff.

apWMMBssParamTXOPLimit.name: apWMMBssParamTXOPLimit
apWMMBssParamTXOPLimit.description: This attribute shall specify the maximum time of an TXOP in units of 32 microseconds for a given AC at a non-AP QSTA.

apWMMBssParamAdmissionControl.name: apWMMBssParamAdmissionControl
apWMMBssParamAdmissionControl.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that admission control is mandatory for the given AC. When False, this attribute indicates that the admission control is not mandatory for the given AC. The default value for this parameter shall be FALSE.

apWMMApParamTable.name: apWMMApParamTable
apWMMApParamTable.description: Conceptual table for EDCA default parameter values at the QAP. This table shall contain the four entries of the EDCA parameters corresponding to four possible ACs (access category): 1) AC_BE (best effort, ACI=0) 2) AC_BK (background, ACI=1) 3) AC_VI (video, ACI=2) 4) AC_VO (voice, ACI=3)

apWMMApParamEntry.name: apWMMApParamEntry
apWMMApParamEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the apWMMApParamTable. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

apWMMApParamIndex.name: apWMMApParamIndex
apWMMApParamIndex.description: The index used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the apWMMApParam Table. The value of this variable is 1) 1 AC_BE (best effort, ACI=0) 2) 2 AC_BK (background, ACI=1) 3) 3 AC_VI (video, ACI=2) 4) 4 AC_VO (voice, ACI=3)

apWMMApParamCWmin.name: apWMMApParamCWmin
apWMMApParamCWmin.description: This attribute shall specify the value of the minimum size of the window in the exponent form that shall be used by a QAP for a particular AC for generating a random number for the backoff.

apWMMApParamCWmax.name: apWMMApParamCWmax
apWMMApParamCWmax.description: This attribute shall specify the value of the maximum size of the window in the exponent form that shall be used by a QAP for a particular AC for generating a random number for the backoff.

apWMMApParamAIFSN.name: apWMMApParamAIFSN
apWMMApParamAIFSN.description: This attribute shall specify the number of slots, after a SIFS duration, that the QAP, for a particular AC, shall sense the medium idle either before transmitting or executing a backoff.

apWMMApParamTXOPLimit.name: apWMMApParamTXOPLimit
apWMMApParamTXOPLimit.description: This attribute shall specify the maximum time of an TXOP in units of 32 microseconds for a given AC at a QAP.

apWMMApParamAdmissionControl.name: apWMMApParamAdmissionControl
apWMMApParamAdmissionControl.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that admission control is mandatory for the given AC. When False, this attribute indicates that the admission control is not mandatory for the given AC. The default value for this parameter shall be FALSE.

apNotificationDot11MacAddr.name: apNotificationDot11MacAddr
apNotificationDot11MacAddr.description: Mac Address of the affected interface, returned with traps only.

apNotificationDot11Station.name: apNotificationDot11Station
apNotificationDot11Station.description: This attribute holds the MAC address of the wireless station

apNotificationDot11RequestType.name: apNotificationDot11RequestType
apNotificationDot11RequestType.description: This attribute defines the request type sent by the station. Value = 1: Unknown request type Value = 2: Association Request Value = 3: Re-association Request Value = 4: Authentication

apNotificationDot11ReasonCode.name: apNotificationDot11ReasonCode
apNotificationDot11ReasonCode.description: This attribute defines the reason for the failure of an operation. Value = 1: Invalid mode/state Value = 2: Station not authenticated. Value = 3: Internal error Value = 4: Out of sequence frame Value = 5: Un-supported algorithm Value = 6: Invalid frame length Value = 7: WEP is required on the AP Value = 8: WEP not allowed Value = 9: Challenge text mismatch

apNotificationDot11IpAddress.name: apNotificationDot11IpAddress
apNotificationDot11IpAddress.description: This value indicates the IP address of the Access Point

apNotificationDot11AuthenticatorMacAddr.name: apNotificationDot11AuthenticatorMacAddr
apNotificationDot11AuthenticatorMacAddr.description: This attribute holds the MAC address of the authenticator for the AP.

sysSystemUp.name: sysSystemUp
sysSystemUp.description: The system up notification shall be sent when the AP is fully up and running.

sysSystemDown.name: sysSystemDown
sysSystemDown.description: The system down notification shall be sent before the AP is about to reboot.

sysRadiusServerChanged.name: sysRadiusServerChanged
sysRadiusServerChanged.description: The RADIUS server changed notification shall be sent when the RADIUS server has changed from Primary / Secondary to Secondary / Primary.

dot11StationAssociation.name: dot11StationAssociation
dot11StationAssociation.description: The associate notification shall be sent when a station successfully associates with the Access Point. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has associated.

dot11StationReAssociation.name: dot11StationReAssociation
dot11StationReAssociation.description: The re-associate notification shall be sent when a station successfully re-associates with the Access Point. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has associated.

dot11StationAuthentication.name: dot11StationAuthentication
dot11StationAuthentication.description: The authentication notification shall be sent when a station successfully authenticates with the Access Point. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

dot11StationRequestFail.name: dot11StationRequestFail
dot11StationRequestFail.description: The station request fail shall be sent out when a station fails to associate / re-associate / authenticate with the Access Point. The notification shall include the MAC address of the station and the reason code for the failure.

dot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess.name: dot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess
dot1xMacAddrAuthSuccess.description: The 802.1X MAC address authentication success notification shall be sent when a station successfully authenticates the MAC address with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

dot1xMacAddrAuthFail.name: dot1xMacAddrAuthFail
dot1xMacAddrAuthFail.description: The 802.1X MAC address authentication failure notification shall be sent when a station fails to authenticate the MAC address with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that failed to authenticate.

dot1xAuthNotInitiated.name: dot1xAuthNotInitiated
dot1xAuthNotInitiated.description: The 802.1X authentication not initiated notification shall be sent when a station did not initiate 802.1X authentication with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that did not initiate 802.1X authentication.

dot1xAuthSuccess.name: dot1xAuthSuccess
dot1xAuthSuccess.description: The 802.1X authentication success notification shall be sent when a station successfully authenticates with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

dot1xAuthFail.name: dot1xAuthFail
dot1xAuthFail.description: The 802.1X authentication failure notification shall be sent when a station fails to authenticate with the RADIUS server. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that failed to authenticate.

localMacAddrAuthSuccess.name: localMacAddrAuthSuccess
localMacAddrAuthSuccess.description: The Local MAC address authentication success notification shall be sent when a station successfully authenticates the MAC address with the database stored locally within the AP. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

localMacAddrAuthFail.name: localMacAddrAuthFail
localMacAddrAuthFail.description: The Local MAC address authentication failure notification shall be sent when a station fails to authenticate the MAC address with the database stored locally within the AP. The value of the notification shall include the MAC address of the station that has authenticated.

pppLogonFail.name: pppLogonFail
pppLogonFail.description: The PPP Logon failure notification shall be sent out when the AP fails to login successfully to the PPP peer using the supplied username and password.

iappStationRoamedFrom.name: iappStationRoamedFrom
iappStationRoamedFrom.description: The IAPP Station Roamed-From Notification shall be sent out whenever a station roams from another Access Point (AP) to this AP. The notification shall include the MAC address of the station and the IP address of the old AP.

iappStationRoamedTo.name: iappStationRoamedTo
iappStationRoamedTo.description: The IAPP Station Roamed-To Notification shall be sent out whenever a station roams to another Access Point (AP) from this AP. The notification shall include the MAC address of the station and the IP address of the new AP.

iappContextDataSent.name: iappContextDataSent
iappContextDataSent.description: The IAPP Context Data Sent notification shall be sent out whenever the context data for a station has been sent to the new AP with which the station has associated. The notification shall include the MAC address of the station and the IP address of the new AP.

sntpServerFail.name: sntpServerFail
sntpServerFail.description: The sntpServerFail notification shall be sent when the AP fails to get time from the configured SNTP server.

dot11InterfaceAFail.name: dot11InterfaceAFail
dot11InterfaceAFail.description: The InterfaceAFail notification shall be sent out when 802.11a wireless interface has failed.

dot11InterfaceGFail.name: dot11InterfaceGFail
dot11InterfaceGFail.description: The InterfaceGFail notification shall be sent out when 802.11g wireless interface has failed.

dot11WirelessSTPDetection.name: dot11WirelessSTPDetection
dot11WirelessSTPDetection.description: The WirelessSTPDetection notification shall be sent out when wireless STP packet has detected.
